Key Match Events: Aaron Nola's command was off, leading to a 9-5 loss for the Phillies against the Marlins.
Garrett Stubbs reached base twice with bunts, including a Little League triple and an RBI single.
Stubbs caught a popup in foul territory to end a troublesome fifth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Aaron Nola reflected on his performance, noting he was 'a little out of sync' and struggled with command.
Garrett Stubbs discussed his strategy of bunting to help the team score runs.
Marlins manager Skip Schumaker acknowledged Nola's off day but praised him as a really good pitcher.
